&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Account Executive, Growth (US)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: &lt;/strong&gt;Boston, MA OR Austin, TX (US)&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Team:&lt;/strong&gt; Sales&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Employment Type:&lt;/strong&gt; Full-Time&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About VulnCheck&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;VulnCheck is transforming vulnerability intelligence by helping security teams act faster and with more confidence. Our platform delivers early, high-quality exploit intelligence, deep asset correlation, and contextual insights to help organizations stay ahead of emerging threats.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for a Growth Account Executive (mid-market, commercial) based in Austin or Boston to join VulnCheck&#39;s fast-growing team. This is a high-velocity hunter role built for a seller who thrives on shorter sales cycles, strong outbound motion, and building pipeline from the ground up in an early-stage cyber company.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll focus on driving net-new revenue across mid-market and commercial accounts, expanding VulnCheck&#39;s footprint with security teams who need actionable vulnerability intelligence to stay ahead of threats.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own a high-velocity book of mid-market and commercial accounts, with a relentless focus on net-new revenue.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive outbound prospecting and build pipeline through targeted outreach, partner collaboration, and inbound follow-up.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage a high volume of opportunities across multiple stages with accurate forecasting in Salesforce.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the full sales cycle—from first contact through negotiation and close—with efficiency and urgency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build relationships with Vulnerability Management leaders, Security Engineers, SOC teams, and IT leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Sales Engineering and Marketing to tailor demos and messaging to prospect needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a credible voice in vulnerability intelligence, helping prospects connect VulnCheck&#39;s capabilities to their real-world risk.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You might be a great fit if you:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have 3+ years of sales experience in cybersecurity, with a track record of hitting or exceeding quota.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Are energized by outbound prospecting and building pipeline from scratch.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Can run fast, efficient sales cycles while managing a high volume of active opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Are confident navigating procurement and negotiating contracts at the mid-market level.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Thrive in fast-paced startup or scale-up environments where the playbook is still being written.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate clearly and persuasively, both written and verbally.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Are comfortable with modern sales tools and CRM systems (e.g., Salesforce, Outreach, LinkedIn Sales Navigator).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications (Required)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience selling within one or more of the following domains:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attack Surface Management (ASM)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Vulnerability Management (VM)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cyber Threat Intelligence (CTI)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated ability to build and manage pipeline independently.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience selling into security organizations at the mid-market or commercial level.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with vulnerability feeds, CVE scoring systems, or exploit intelligence.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working in hybrid or distributed teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Apply Now&amp;nb

&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bookkeeper&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: &lt;/strong&gt;US Remote (preferred Oregon, Austin, or Boston)&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Team: &lt;/strong&gt;Finance&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Employment Type:&lt;/strong&gt; Full-Time&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About VulnCheck&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;VulnCheck is transforming vulnerability intelligence by helping security teams act faster and with more confidence. Our platform delivers early, high-quality exploit intelligence, deep asset correlation, and contextual insights to help organizations stay ahead of emerging threats.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;We&#39;re looking for an organized, detail-oriented Bookkeeper to support our Controller with the day-to-day financial operations of a growing SaaS company. You&#39;ll assist with core accounting functions — from Accounts Payable/Receivable to month-end close — and help ensure our books remain accurate as we scale.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is ideal for someone who takes pride in clean books, thrives on routine, and wants to grow within a finance team at a tech company. This is a 100% remote role with preference for candidates based in either Portland, Boston, or Austin.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support with accounts payable, accounts receivable, and general ledger activity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with monthly balance sheet reconciliations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare and post journal entries as needed for period-end closes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in preparing supporting schedules for financial statements as needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support during external audits&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain organized records and supporting documentation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flag process gaps and support the Controller in implementing workflow improvements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Bring:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in Accounting or Finance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3 - 5 years of accounting experience, with meaningful exposure to SaaS or tech industry&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of GAAP&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with accounts payable and accounts receivable workflows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in Quickbooks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in Ramp or other bill pay systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in Excel and Google Sheets (pivot tables, VLOOKUPs, etc)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience leveraging AI-assisted tools to support day-to-day tasks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must be tech-savy and comfortable learning new tools and software&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High attention to detail and data accuracy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must have the ability to manage high transaction volume accurately&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable operating independently in a fast-moving environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bonus: Cybersecurity experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
