&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Finance Engineer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: &lt;/strong&gt;Boston&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Team: &lt;/strong&gt;Finance&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Employment Type:&lt;/strong&gt; Full-Time&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About VulnCheck&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;VulnCheck is transforming vulnerability intelligence by helping security teams act faster and with more confidence. Our platform delivers early, high-quality exploit intelligence, deep asset correlation, and contextual insights to help organizations stay ahead of emerging threats.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There&#39;s a new archetype taking shape in finance: someone who pairs real finance judgment with the ability to build their own solutions — wiring AI agents into the GL, standing up data pipelines without filing an engineering ticket, automating workflows end to end instead of running them by hand. VulnCheck&#39;s finance function is scaling across three entities (US, UK, Singapore), and we need someone who builds the systems and AI-driven workflows that keep Finance accurate and fast as we outgrow manual process. That means being genuinely fluent with LLMs (we use Claude) as a working tool, comfortable enough with SQL and APIs to connect our GL, billing, CRM, and spend data without waiting on engineering, and grounded enough in accounting judgment to know when an automated output is right or wrong. You&#39;ll turn raw data into automated models, pipelines, and live dashboards that leadership actually use to make decisions, with the audit trail to back it up.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;AI-driven close &amp;amp; reporting workflows.&lt;/strong&gt; Build Claude-powered workflows that draft variance commentary, flag anomalies, and assemble reporting packages.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Financial systems &amp;amp; pipelines. &lt;/strong&gt;Connect our GL, billing, CRM, and spend management systems into a single source of truth for ARR, cash, and unit economics, through API/MCPconnections you own rather than tickets you file.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Model infrastructure.&lt;/strong&gt; Own the technical architecture behind the financial model, including version control, forecast wiring, and scenario logic, so it stops needing a manual rebuild every quarter.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dashboards &amp;amp; reporting automation.&lt;/strong&gt; Build self-serve dashboards for ARR roll-forward, cohort retention, burn multiple, and deferred revenue that are live and drillable instead of rebuilt by hand each cycle.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Close automation. &lt;/strong&gt;Take manual steps out of the monthly and quarterly close through scripting, AI agents, and system integration.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Audit &amp;amp; controls support.&lt;/strong&gt; Build documented, repeatable data workflows that hold up under external audit scrutiny (ASC 606, ASC 830, transfer pricing). Automated doesn&#39;t mean uncontrolled.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross-functional data requests. &lt;/strong&gt;Be the technical bridge between Finance and GTM, RevOps, and Engineering when a question just needs someone to query the data instead of waiting on someone else to pull it.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Bring&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;LLM fluency: real, daily use of Claude (or similar) to analyze data, draft narratives, and check outputs against source documents. You&#39;re comfortable building and iterating on prompts, skills, and agents, not just asking one-off questions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Workflow automation: you&#39;ve actually found a manual, recurring process and killed it, not just wanted to.&lt;/

&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;On Site Systems Administrator (US)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Maryland&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Team: &lt;/strong&gt;Research&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Employment Type:&lt;/strong&gt; Full-Time&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About VulnCheck&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;VulnCheck is transforming vulnerability intelligence by helping security teams act faster and with more confidence. Our platform delivers early, high-quality exploit intelligence, deep asset correlation, and contextual insights to help organizations stay ahead of emerging threats.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;While this is a hybrid role, the position requires regular onsite management of physical lab equipment in Baltimore area on call off hours and weekends.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;VulnCheck is looking for a Systems Administrator / Lab Manager to build, maintain, and operate the lab infrastructure that supports our vulnerability research team. This role is responsible for standing up and managing a research environment that includes networking equipment, IoT / OT devices, and the supporting compute, storage, and network infrastructure our researchers depend on to discover, analyze, and validate vulnerabilities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll work closely with our exploit developers and threat researchers to ensure they have reliable, secure, and reproducible environments for testing against real-world hardware and software. The lab is central to VulnCheck&#39;s mission — our researchers need to move fast, and the infrastructure has to keep up.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, build, and maintain the physical and virtual lab infrastructure used by VulnCheck&#39;s vulnerability research team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Procure, configure, and manage networking equipment (routers, switches, firewalls, wireless access points) and IoT / OT devices used for security research and exploit validation.&lt;/li&gt;
